00:33:47,257 --> 00:33:49,257
Cold case.

271
00:33:49,259 --> 00:33:50,792
I have clearance
to take it out.

272
00:33:50,794 --> 00:33:52,561
You don't.

273
00:33:52,563 --> 00:33:54,799
So, what,
you're going to report me?

274
00:33:59,670 --> 00:34:01,635
Eli Kvale.

275
00:34:01,637 --> 00:34:02,572
Tell me.

276
00:34:05,142 --> 00:34:07,142
She was married.

277
00:34:07,144 --> 00:34:09,411
She had three children.

278
00:34:09,413 --> 00:34:11,813
The 12th of November,
six years ago,

279
00:34:11,815 --> 00:34:14,249
she went missing.

280
00:34:14,251 --> 00:34:17,155
And the day she vanished,
it was snowing.

281
00:34:19,222 --> 00:34:23,224
Hege Dahl disappeared
the eighth of November.

282
00:34:23,226 --> 00:34:26,293
The day she went missing,
it was snowing.

283
00:34:26,295 --> 00:34:28,329
Not unusual. It's winter.

284
00:34:28,331 --> 00:34:29,597
Now Birte Becker.

285
00:34:29,599 --> 00:34:32,434
The night she disappeared...

286
00:34:32,436 --> 00:34:34,603
- Snowing.
- Yeah.

287
00:34:34,605 --> 00:34:38,440
I think it's the falling snow
that sets the killer off.

288
00:34:38,442 --> 00:34:40,275
And furthermore,
they're all married,

289
00:34:40,277 --> 00:34:41,612
they all have children.

290
00:34:44,514 --> 00:34:47,581
Did you talk to Filip Becker?

291
00:34:47,583 --> 00:34:50,251
Nine times out of ten,
the husband did it.

292
00:34:50,253 --> 00:34:52,287
He was interviewed,
and his alibi is solid.

293
00:34:52,289 --> 00:34:54,258
He was a hundred miles away.

294
00:34:56,592 --> 00:34:58,459
Have you eaten?

295
00:34:58,461 --> 00:35:00,195
No.

296
00:35:00,197 --> 00:35:01,766
No, I haven't. I'm hungry.

297
00:35:12,409 --> 00:35:14,708
28th, handball.

298
00:35:14,710 --> 00:35:16,680
Josephine's handball match.

299
00:35:19,449 --> 00:35:22,583
Third, "F. lunch."

300
00:35:22,585 --> 00:35:26,188
That's lunch
with her friend Frida.

301
00:35:26,190 --> 00:35:28,657
I really... I don't see
the point in doing this.

302
00:35:28,659 --> 00:35:30,628
I won't keep you much longer.

303
00:35:33,829 --> 00:35:35,229
Ninth, Vetlesen.

304
00:35:35,231 --> 00:35:37,566
He's her doctor.
Tenth, yoga.

305
00:35:37,568 --> 00:35:39,967
Do you have any idea
why your wife went to see him?

306
00:35:39,969 --> 00:35:41,536
Who?

307
00:35:41,538 --> 00:35:43,474
Dr. Vetlesen.

308
00:35:44,875 --> 00:35:46,409
No.

309
00:35:47,510 --> 00:35:48,709
Tenth, yoga.

310
00:35:48,711 --> 00:35:50,579
Is there any reason
you can think of

311
00:35:50,581 --> 00:35:54,352
why your wife
might disappear so suddenly?

312
00:35:57,554 --> 00:36:00,222
Your marriage...

313
00:36:00,224 --> 00:36:02,527
was everything all right?

314
00:36:06,862 --> 00:36:08,963
Were either of you
having an affair?

315
00:36:08,965 --> 00:36:11,233
Daddy!

316
00:36:11,235 --> 00:36:12,666
Come on!

317
00:36:12,668 --> 00:36:14,568
I promised her we'd walk
around the neighborhood

318
00:36:14,570 --> 00:36:17,371
to see if we could find
her mother.

319
00:36:17,373 --> 00:36:18,773
I'm just gonna get my jacket,
darling!

320
00:36:18,775 --> 00:36:20,675
Come out!

321
00:36:20,677 --> 00:36:22,276
Dad!

322
00:37:01,818 --> 00:37:03,521
Step inside.

323
00:37:19,402 --> 00:37:22,839
Mm. I thought
you wouldn't remember.

324
00:37:28,344 --> 00:37:31,479
Is he still
giving you a hard time?

325
00:37:31,481 --> 00:37:33,081
If you want, I can talk to him.

326
00:37:33,083 --> 00:37:35,519
Oh!

327
00:37:38,322 --> 00:37:40,988
Just have fun tonight.

328
00:37:40,990 --> 00:37:43,358
He misses you.

329
00:37:43,360 --> 00:37:44,726
Hi, Harry.

330
00:37:44,728 --> 00:37:46,264
Good to see you.

331
00:37:47,463 --> 00:37:49,032
Sorry I'm late, honey.

332
00:37:51,335 --> 00:37:52,900
Have you had anything to eat?

333
00:37:52,902 --> 00:37:55,070
No, I'll-I'll grab
something later.

334
00:37:55,072 --> 00:37:57,505
No, no, no, I've got vouchers.

335
00:37:57,507 --> 00:37:59,541
- Yeah?
- Yep.

336
00:37:59,543 --> 00:38:01,575
Hot dog or hot dog.

337
00:38:01,577 --> 00:38:03,614
Well, hot dog, then.

338
00:38:04,780 --> 00:38:06,347
Harry?

339
00:38:06,349 --> 00:38:09,019
I'll get something to eat
with Oleg after.

340
00:38:18,728 --> 00:38:21,996
So, how are things with you?

341
00:38:21,998 --> 00:38:23,831
- All right.
- Yeah?

342
00:38:23,833 --> 00:38:25,766
Bit tired.

343
00:38:25,768 --> 00:38:28,471
You've been working too hard,
haven't you?

344
00:38:30,005 --> 00:38:32,042
I can't sleep.

345
00:38:33,909 --> 00:38:35,945
You should try Valzetet.

346
00:38:37,380 --> 00:38:39,613
It's a new one.

347
00:38:39,615 --> 00:38:40,951
It'll help you sleep.

348
00:38:42,552 --> 00:38:45,153
I can give you
a prescription right now.

349
00:38:45,155 --> 00:38:46,755
- Really?
- Yeah.

350
00:38:46,757 --> 00:38:48,155
With that?

351
00:38:48,157 --> 00:38:49,824
Yeah.

352
00:39:01,804 --> 00:39:04,972
She won't allow me
to try and find my father.

353
00:39:04,974 --> 00:39:07,444
Your mother
should be the judge of that.

354
00:39:10,679 --> 00:39:12,746
She won't listen to me.

355
00:39:12,748 --> 00:39:14,584
She's worried about you.

356
00:39:16,452 --> 00:39:18,552
All she cares about is herself.

357
00:39:18,554 --> 00:39:20,155
All she cares about is you.

358
00:39:20,157 --> 00:39:22,624
That's why she dumped me.

359
00:39:22,626 --> 00:39:24,793
I'm such a bad influence.

360
00:39:24,795 --> 00:39:27,461
She's concerned.

361
00:39:27,463 --> 00:39:30,465
Concerned about what?

362
00:39:30,467 --> 00:39:32,603
The fact that you run away
from home.

363
00:39:34,070 --> 00:39:37,037
The fact
that you've been drinking.

364
00:39:37,039 --> 00:39:41,612
So you're gonna give me
a lecture about drinking?

365
00:39:43,012 --> 00:39:44,481
Don't be a prick.

366
00:39:45,849 --> 00:39:47,882
Your mum told me
the school's arranged

367
00:39:47,884 --> 00:39:50,050
a father-and-son camping trip.

368
00:39:50,052 --> 00:39:52,487
If you want, I can come.

369
00:39:52,489 --> 00:39:56,126
But you're not
her boyfriend anymore.

370
00:39:57,059 --> 00:39:58,459
So?

371
00:40:02,231 --> 00:40:03,498
Yeah.

372
00:40:03,500 --> 00:40:05,599
Yeah.

373
00:40:05,601 --> 00:40:06,737
I want you to come.

374
00:40:09,606 --> 00:40:11,742
- You sure?
- Yeah.

375
00:40:12,943 --> 00:40:14,541
Good.

376
00:40:14,543 --> 00:40:18,679
So, what's the...
the big surprise?

377
00:40:18,681 --> 00:40:19,716
Uh...

378
00:40:21,550 --> 00:40:23,650
Let's find out.

379
00:40:23,652 --> 00:40:25,820
Someone at work
got me the tickets.

380
00:40:37,099 --> 00:40:39,666
You got a message.

381
00:40:39,668 --> 00:40:41,538
Let me see what it says.

382
00:40:43,706 --> 00:40:45,974
I gotta make a call.

383
00:40:45,976 --> 00:40:48,642
You stay here?

384
00:40:48,644 --> 00:40:50,545
Harry, there's another

385
00:40:50,547 --> 00:40:51,945
missing woman...
in Geilo this time.

386
00:40:51,947 --> 00:40:53,947
That's not our jurisdiction.

387
00:40:53,949 --> 00:40:55,849
I think we should have
a look at this.

388
00:40:55,851 --> 00:40:57,985
I'm going to be with you
in two minutes, okay?

389
00:40:57,987 --> 00:41:00,657
Her husband specifically
asked for you.

390
00:41:08,164 --> 00:41:10,097
- Hello.
- Hi.

391
00:41:10,099 --> 00:41:12,900
Oh, I didn't expect you
so early.

392
00:41:12,902 --> 00:41:14,836
- Something came up.
- Oh.

393
00:41:14,838 --> 00:41:16,537
Hi, Harry.

394
00:41:16,539 --> 00:41:17,740
- Hi.
- How was the concert?

395
00:41:19,742 --> 00:41:22,545
Yeah, it was... it was great.

396
00:41:24,547 --> 00:41:27,115
We spoke.

397
00:41:27,117 --> 00:41:31,786
I'm taking him on the
father-and-son camping trip...

398
00:41:31,788 --> 00:41:33,755
thing.

399
00:41:33,757 --> 00:41:35,956
Uh...

400
00:41:35,958 --> 00:41:37,659
See you.

401
00:41:37,661 --> 00:41:40,063
- Hey.
- Bye.

402
00:41:44,634 --> 00:41:46,633
Take me home.

403
00:41:46,635 --> 00:41:48,903
We'll go in the morning.

404
00:42:29,378 --> 00:42:31,813
<i>Who reported her missing?</i>

405
00:42:31,815 --> 00:42:33,180
<i>Her husband last night.</i>

406
00:42:33,182 --> 00:42:35,316
<i>20:05.</i>

407
00:42:35,318 --> 00:42:39,019
<i>Sylvia Ottersen, 33 years old.</i>

408
00:42:39,021 --> 00:42:42,990
<i>Self-employed, married twice.</i>

409
00:42:42,992 --> 00:42:44,825
<i>But no children.</i>

410
00:43:01,945 --> 00:43:03,713
Hello?

411
00:43:05,815 --> 00:43:07,050
Hello!

412
00:43:09,818 --> 00:43:11,786
Hello?

413
00:43:44,054 --> 00:43:46,054
- Hi.
- Hi.

414
00:43:46,056 --> 00:43:47,688
Can I help you?

415
00:43:47,690 --> 00:43:50,326
Yeah, well,
we're with the Oslo Police.

416
00:43:52,961 --> 00:43:55,396
We got the
missing persons call.

417
00:43:55,398 --> 00:43:57,768
Oh. Who's missing?

418
00:43:58,867 --> 00:44:00,934
Sylvia Ottersen.

419
00:44:00,936 --> 00:44:02,970
I'm Sylvia Ottersen.

420
00:44:02,972 --> 00:44:05,706
What, you're Sylvia Ottersen?

421
00:44:05,708 --> 00:44:09,177
Why... why would your husband
report you missing?

422
00:44:09,179 --> 00:44:10,778
I have no idea.

423
00:44:10,780 --> 00:44:13,213
He's not the kind
to play practical jokes.

424
00:44:13,215 --> 00:44:15,749
- Is he here?
- No.

425
00:44:15,751 --> 00:44:18,286
He's gone to the station
to pick up my sister.

426
00:44:18,288 --> 00:44:19,787
Okay.

427
00:44:19,789 --> 00:44:22,255
Well, I guess it must be
a crank call.

428
00:44:22,257 --> 00:44:23,858
We didn't know where you were,

429
00:44:23,860 --> 00:44:26,427
so we had a look
inside the house.

430
00:44:26,429 --> 00:44:28,396
I turned your music off.

431
00:44:28,398 --> 00:44:30,067
Sorry about that.

432
00:44:31,835 --> 00:44:33,670
Thank you.

433
00:44:37,440 --> 00:44:40,208
Can I just ask you...
is it just

434
00:44:40,210 --> 00:44:42,112
you and your husband,
or do you have any children?

435
00:44:44,213 --> 00:44:46,182
No, it's just us.

436
00:44:47,817 --> 00:44:50,253
Okay. Thank you.

437
00:45:04,800 --> 00:45:06,800
<i>What the hell
do you think you're doing?</i>

438
00:45:06,802 --> 00:45:10,771
You know damn well
what I'm talking about.

439
00:45:10,773 --> 00:45:13,775
Calling the police,
telling them I'm missing.

440
00:45:13,777 --> 00:45:16,209
You think that's funny?

441
00:45:16,211 --> 00:45:18,211
Don't you understand?
It's over.

442
00:45:18,213 --> 00:45:20,116
I don't want to see you again.

443
00:45:21,384 --> 00:45:23,316
No, it wasn't your child.

444
00:45:23,318 --> 00:45:25,552
It was mine.

445
00:45:25,554 --> 00:45:28,891
If you call one more time,
I'm going to the police.

446
00:46:42,431 --> 00:46:44,932
<i>HQ to DC Bratt.</i>

447
00:46:44,934 --> 00:46:46,499
<i>DC Bratt?</i>

448
00:46:46,501 --> 00:46:48,235
<i>Yeah, speaking.</i>

449
00:46:48,237 --> 00:46:49,970
<i>We've had
a missing persons report.</i>

450
00:46:49,972 --> 00:46:52,072
<i>A woman named Sylvia Ottersen.</i>

451
00:46:52,074 --> 00:46:55,342
<i>Oh, no, she's fine.
We-we just left her.</i>

452
00:46:55,344 --> 00:46:59,179
<i>Well, the call
came in two minutes ago.</i>

453
00:46:59,181 --> 00:47:02,083
<i>Her husband asked specifically
for Inspector Hole.</i>

454
00:47:02,085 --> 00:47:04,619
<i>How could...</i>

455
00:47:04,621 --> 00:47:06,423
<i>Turn the car around.</i>

456
00:47:23,106 --> 00:47:25,042
Sylvia?

457
00:47:27,110 --> 00:47:29,476
Sorry we're back,
Mrs. Ottersen.

458
00:47:29,478 --> 00:47:32,079
We just wanted to make sure
you were all right.

459
00:47:32,081 --> 00:47:34,148
I'm Ann Pedersen.

460
00:47:34,150 --> 00:47:36,284
Sylvia's my sister.

461
00:47:36,286 --> 00:47:38,286
We're twins.

462
00:47:38,288 --> 00:47:39,556
Who are you?

463
00:49:16,018 --> 00:49:19,387
- Is that enough?
- Yeah, keep going.

464
00:49:19,389 --> 00:49:21,155
Did you find Hagen?

465
00:49:21,157 --> 00:49:23,523
He's at the dinner
at City Hall.

466
00:49:23,525 --> 00:49:25,428
Let's keep it clear,
if you can.

467
00:49:41,643 --> 00:49:43,312
<i>She was a free spirit.</i>

468
00:49:46,615 --> 00:49:49,119
And she always liked men.

469
00:49:50,452 --> 00:49:52,255
Ever since we were teenagers.

470
00:49:55,090 --> 00:49:57,193
She was a good person.

471
00:49:58,460 --> 00:50:00,827
She didn't want to hurt anyone.

472
00:50:00,829 --> 00:50:03,333
It's just the way she was.

473
00:50:08,737 --> 00:50:12,472
I know your sister
didn't have any children.

474
00:50:12,474 --> 00:50:14,108
It was just that there
was something

475
00:50:14,110 --> 00:50:15,608
in her reaction
that when I asked...

476
00:50:15,610 --> 00:50:17,646
She was pregnant.

477
00:50:20,349 --> 00:50:23,387
She wasn't sure
who the father was.

478
00:50:27,190 --> 00:50:30,027
She got rid of the baby
a few weeks ago.

479
00:50:59,521 --> 00:51:01,222
This way, please.

480
00:51:01,224 --> 00:51:03,389
Thank you very much.
That's it.

481
00:51:17,739 --> 00:51:19,673
Ladies and gentlemen,

482
00:51:19,675 --> 00:51:21,508
introducing our guest of honor,

483
00:51:21,510 --> 00:51:24,144
king of industry,
philanthropist,

484
00:51:24,146 --> 00:51:26,880
and head of Oslo's
Winter Games bid,

485
00:51:26,882 --> 00:51:29,483
Arve Stop.

486
00:51:29,485 --> 00:51:31,818
So lovely of you
to be here for us.

487
00:51:31,820 --> 00:51:33,521
I'm not on the list, but I know
many of these people.

488
00:51:33,523 --> 00:51:34,521
I'm supposed to be on the list.

489
00:51:34,523 --> 00:51:38,258
I'm a close, old friend
of Arve Stop's, you see.

490
00:51:38,260 --> 00:51:40,193
- There's been some kind of misunderstanding.
- I have a...

491
00:51:40,195 --> 00:51:41,327
- a person named Vetlesen.
- Come on up.

492
00:51:41,329 --> 00:51:42,295
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
you can come here.

493
00:51:42,297 --> 00:51:45,231
He says he's
a friend of Arve Stop.

494
00:51:45,233 --> 00:51:47,700
- No. Wait, wait.
- No, it's fine, it's fine.

495
00:51:47,702 --> 00:51:49,639
No, just relax, just relax.

496
00:51:52,307 --> 00:51:54,474
I run over a dozen companies.

497
00:51:54,476 --> 00:51:56,242
When people ask me why

498
00:51:56,244 --> 00:51:59,679
I've given up so much
of my time to lead this bid,

499
00:51:59,681 --> 00:52:03,450
I tell them it's because I
never had these opportunities.

500
00:52:03,452 --> 00:52:07,521
When I was a boy, the only
winter sports I engaged in

501
00:52:07,523 --> 00:52:09,657
were the uphill snow shovel

502
00:52:09,659 --> 00:52:12,258
and the 50-meter
firewood carry.

503
00:52:16,231 --> 00:52:20,367
That is why I believe
passionately that this Cup

504
00:52:20,369 --> 00:52:24,441
is about much more than just
publicity for our fair city.

505
00:52:34,349 --> 00:52:35,615
Homicides?

506
00:52:35,617 --> 00:52:37,251
Just missing persons for now,

507
00:52:37,253 --> 00:52:38,851
but the pattern is disturbing.

508
00:52:38,853 --> 00:52:40,787
And...

509
00:52:40,789 --> 00:52:43,425
I received this.

510
00:52:47,429 --> 00:52:48,697
Prints?

511
00:52:49,864 --> 00:52:51,565
It isn't just the letter.

512
00:52:51,567 --> 00:52:54,001
He reported her missing
before he killed her.

513
00:52:54,003 --> 00:52:56,273
He was watching us
the entire time.

514
00:52:59,307 --> 00:53:00,773
What do you need?

515
00:53:00,775 --> 00:53:02,508
Small team.

516
00:53:02,510 --> 00:53:04,445
I'll set up a separate
incident room at the mill.

517
00:53:04,447 --> 00:53:06,646
All right, but I don't want
a word of this to be leaked...

518
00:53:06,648 --> 00:53:08,782
- To the press.
- Press, yeah.

519
00:53:08,784 --> 00:53:11,387
Not until this fucking bid
is over.

520
00:53:50,559 --> 00:53:54,531
Does this strike you as the
proper time and place for this?

521
00:53:56,666 --> 00:53:58,401
Wait.

522
00:54:21,489 --> 00:54:22,822
Idiot.

523
00:54:22,824 --> 00:54:24,590
What?

524
00:54:24,592 --> 00:54:26,392
Arve?

525
00:54:26,394 --> 00:54:28,628
What? No, don't cry.

526
00:54:28,630 --> 00:54:31,033
Listen, what...

527
00:54:38,407 --> 00:54:39,776
Shit.

528
00:54:59,128 --> 00:55:00,563
Hey.

529
00:55:01,697 --> 00:55:02,899
Hey!

530
00:55:09,538 --> 00:55:10,773
Get out.

531
00:55:11,873 --> 00:55:13,509
Get out!

532
00:55:29,858 --> 00:55:31,460
Hey.

533
00:55:32,561 --> 00:55:34,862
Oi, mate!

534
00:55:34,864 --> 00:55:37,998
Annette Elden, 33,

535
00:55:38,000 --> 00:55:41,101
disappeared
12th of December, 2006.

536
00:55:41,103 --> 00:55:43,737
Her head washed ashore
near Arendal.

537
00:55:43,739 --> 00:55:46,472
