What? Oleg?

1060
01:40:01,427 --> 01:40:03,564
He... he's at school.

1061
01:40:05,064 --> 01:40:07,231
And Harry?

1062
01:40:07,233 --> 01:40:09,400
Is Harry here?

1063
01:40:11,104 --> 01:40:12,437
No.

1064
01:40:12,439 --> 01:40:13,740
Oh.

1065
01:40:16,176 --> 01:40:19,380
How did he convince you
to give him those pills?

1066
01:40:20,479 --> 01:40:22,081
He didn't.

1067
01:40:23,649 --> 01:40:25,715
You didn't have
to do it for me.

1068
01:40:25,717 --> 01:40:27,520
I didn't do it for you.

1069
01:40:37,529 --> 01:40:39,766
It was never about you.

1070
01:40:52,878 --> 01:40:55,213
I'm outside his house.

1071
01:40:55,215 --> 01:40:56,714
I can't reach Rakel.

1072
01:40:56,716 --> 01:40:58,719
Send someone to her apartment.

1073
01:41:22,876 --> 01:41:24,342
Oleg.

1074
01:41:24,344 --> 01:41:26,079
Sorry to keep you waiting.

1075
01:41:46,365 --> 01:41:48,534
Why do you have Mom's phone?

1076
01:41:52,471 --> 01:41:54,205
Come on.

1077
01:42:09,956 --> 01:42:12,192
You and I have more in common
than you think.

1078
01:42:15,360 --> 01:42:17,631
I didn't know
who my father was, either.

1079
01:42:35,948 --> 01:42:38,284
Magnus, track Rakel's phone.

1080
01:42:49,261 --> 01:42:50,827
Sorry, I just...

1081
01:42:56,235 --> 01:42:57,371
All right.

1082
01:42:59,439 --> 01:43:00,972
Okay, Harry, we just
picked up her signal,

1083
01:43:00,974 --> 01:43:02,940
<i>heading west towards Telemark.</i>

1084
01:43:02,942 --> 01:43:04,909
<i>It is a red Volvo,</i>

1085
01:43:04,911 --> 01:43:07,277
<i>registered to
a Mathias Lund-Helgesen,</i>

1086
01:43:07,279 --> 01:43:09,649
Rjukan, 2421.

1087
01:43:11,884 --> 01:43:13,683
<i>The house is pretty remote.</i>

1088
01:43:13,685 --> 01:43:15,518
There's-there's an access road,
but that's it.

1089
01:43:15,520 --> 01:43:17,521
And there's a big lake
around it.

1090
01:43:17,523 --> 01:43:19,889
<i>Helicopters are grounded
because of the weather,</i>

1091
01:43:19,891 --> 01:43:21,862
<i>but Delta is on their way.</i>

1092
01:43:24,564 --> 01:43:26,630
<i>Anything on Mathias's family?</i>

1093
01:43:26,632 --> 01:43:28,299
<i>Okay, I've got something here.</i>

1094
01:43:28,301 --> 01:43:30,433
Jonas Lund-Helgesen,
former police officer,

1095
01:43:30,435 --> 01:43:32,836
lost his job in '89.

1096
01:43:32,838 --> 01:43:36,374
A scandal involving
a woman drowning in a car.

1097
01:43:36,376 --> 01:43:37,708
Probable suicide.

1098
01:43:37,710 --> 01:43:40,644
- <i>She had a son.</i>
- Stop!

1099
01:43:40,646 --> 01:43:42,580
<i>Father unknown.</i>

1100
01:43:42,582 --> 01:43:43,781
Please!

1101
01:43:43,783 --> 01:43:45,482
<i>He was sent to an orphanage.</i>

1102
01:43:52,292 --> 01:43:54,458
<i>Who led the investigation</i>

1103
01:43:54,460 --> 01:43:56,460
<i>into the woman's disappearance?</i>

1104
01:43:56,462 --> 01:43:59,296
<i>Some local talent
in the village nearby.</i>

1105
01:43:59,298 --> 01:44:00,563
<i>What's his name?</i>

1106
01:44:00,565 --> 01:44:02,536
<i>Jonas Lund-Helgesen.</i>

1107
01:44:03,636 --> 01:44:05,969
Jonas! No!

1108
01:44:05,971 --> 01:44:07,506
Please stop!

1109
01:44:26,426 --> 01:44:28,262
<i>Harry?</i>

1110
01:44:29,362 --> 01:44:30,697
Harry? We've lost him.

1111
01:46:28,948 --> 01:46:30,884
Sit down, Harry.

1112
01:46:42,194 --> 01:46:43,630
Pass me the gun.

1113
01:46:53,706 --> 01:46:55,708
I didn't think you'd find me.

1114
01:46:59,110 --> 01:47:01,581
Perhaps the pills helped
after all.

1115
01:47:03,515 --> 01:47:05,985
I spoke to Filip Becker.

1116
01:47:08,887 --> 01:47:10,920
What's going to happen

1117
01:47:10,922 --> 01:47:14,795
when Josephine Becker
finds out he isn't her father?

1118
01:47:16,194 --> 01:47:18,728
She'll still love him.

1119
01:47:18,730 --> 01:47:19,765
Wrong answer.

1120
01:47:30,743 --> 01:47:32,512
Let's try again.

1121
01:47:33,779 --> 01:47:35,879
Was it right
for Sylvia Ottersen

1122
01:47:35,881 --> 01:47:38,048
to kill her unborn child

1123
01:47:38,050 --> 01:47:40,150
simply because
she couldn't keep track

1124
01:47:40,152 --> 01:47:42,189
of who the father was?

1125
01:47:43,989 --> 01:47:45,992
That was her choice.

1126
01:47:48,694 --> 01:47:49,960
Too short.

1127
01:47:49,962 --> 01:47:52,532
Maybe she was afraid.

1128
01:47:56,135 --> 01:47:58,204
What about you, Harry?

1129
01:47:59,971 --> 01:48:01,841
You have a woman who loves you.

1130
01:48:02,975 --> 01:48:04,778
A boy who's devoted to you.

1131
01:48:06,578 --> 01:48:08,881
Why did you abandon them?

1132
01:48:11,317 --> 01:48:13,317
They deserve better.

1133
01:48:14,854 --> 01:48:16,722
Too easy.

1134
01:48:18,090 --> 01:48:19,924
Because...

1135
01:48:19,926 --> 01:48:21,761
I'm selfish.

1136
01:48:24,229 --> 01:48:25,931
I'm an addict.

1137
01:48:28,935 --> 01:48:31,738
There isn't enough room
for them.

1138
01:48:47,920 --> 01:48:51,257
You know, when I first saw
your picture in the papers...

1139
01:48:53,059 --> 01:48:56,660
...with all those medals,

1140
01:48:56,662 --> 01:49:01,967
I thought, "That man
must have a perfect family."

1141
01:49:07,038 --> 01:49:08,974
And here you are.

1142
01:49:10,141 --> 01:49:11,978
Last question.

1143
01:49:13,845 --> 01:49:18,317
This boy, who doesn't even know
who his father is...

1144
01:49:19,918 --> 01:49:22,018
...who's had to put up
with so many men

1145
01:49:22,020 --> 01:49:24,724
like you and me
taking his place...

1146
01:49:28,761 --> 01:49:31,064
...does his mother
deserve to live?

1147
01:49:35,234 --> 01:49:38,071
Why don't you ask him?

1148
01:50:22,148 --> 01:50:23,817
You all right?

1149
01:50:27,185 --> 01:50:30,023
Kill him. Kill him.

1150
01:50:31,122 --> 01:50:32,291
Kill him!

1151
01:51:08,793 --> 01:51:10,095
Come on!

1152
01:51:11,930 --> 01:51:14,164
I'm ready!

1153
01:51:14,166 --> 01:51:16,133
I'm here!

1154
01:51:16,135 --> 01:51:17,401
Come on!

1155
01:51:50,101 --> 01:51:52,204
I know why you blame her.

1156
01:52:02,981 --> 01:52:05,385
You've been wrong
the whole time.

1157
01:52:12,024 --> 01:52:13,960
<i>It wasn't her.</i>

1158
01:52:19,131 --> 01:52:23,002
It wasn't your mother
who didn't want you.

1159
01:52:24,936 --> 01:52:26,872
<i>It was your father.</i>

1160
01:52:30,141 --> 01:52:32,912
It would have been better
for him...

1161
01:52:36,114 --> 01:52:37,850
...had you not been born.

1162
01:54:00,431 --> 01:54:02,232
The pathologist detected traces

1163
01:54:02,234 --> 01:54:04,233
of the drug Ketanome.

1164
01:54:04,235 --> 01:54:06,335
But the direct cause of death
was drowning

1165
01:54:06,337 --> 01:54:08,571
as a result of blood
filling her lungs.

1166
01:54:08,573 --> 01:54:11,441
24 stab wounds
were found in her mouth,

1167
01:54:11,443 --> 01:54:13,277
all at regular intervals,

1168
01:54:13,279 --> 01:54:15,278
and at the same depth...
seven centimeters.

1169
01:54:15,280 --> 01:54:16,679
Pathologist can't determine

1170
01:54:16,681 --> 01:54:18,384
what kind of weapon was used.

1171
01:54:20,019 --> 01:54:22,585
And he's never seen
anything like it.

1172
01:54:22,587 --> 01:54:25,187
I'll take it.

1173
01:54:27,127 --> 01:54:32,127
Subtitles by explosiveskull
